on, Philip. (1974), ''A Matter of Honour: An Account of the Indian Army, its Officers and Men'', Macmillan\n* {{cite book|last=McCosh|first=John |authorlink=John McCosh|title=[[s:Advice to Officers in India|Advice to Officers in India]]|year=1856|publisher=Wm. H. Allen & Co.|location=London|edition=revised}}\n* Omissi, David. ''The Sepoy and the Raj: The Indian Army, 1860\u20131940'' (London: Macmillan, 1994)\n* Roy, Pinaki. \u201c''Black Peepers who charged'': Remembering the British-Indian Military Personnel of the Two World Wars\u201d. ''Modernity of India: Ambiguities and Deformities''. Eds. Sarkar, A.K., K. Chakraborty, and M. Dutta. [[Kolkata]]: Setu Prakashani, 2014 ({{ISBN|978-93-80677-68-2}}). pp.&nbsp;181\u201396.\n\n===Primary sources===\n*  Cross, J. P., and Buddhiman Gurung, eds. ''Gurkhas at War in Their Own Words: The Gurkha Experience 1939 to the Present'' (London: Greenhill, 2002),\n* [[John Masters|Masters, John]] (1956). ''Bugles and a Tiger'': Viking. (autobiographical account of his service as a junior British officer in a Gurkha regiment in the years leading up to World War II)\n* Omissi, David E. ed. ''Indian Voices of the Great War: Soldiers' Letters, 1914\u201318'' (1999)\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|British Indian Army}}\n\n* IFSCFR: [https://www.ifscfr.org/ Remembering World War 1] \u2013 Unsung Indian Heroes of WWI\n*David Steinburg, [http://www.houseofdavid.ca/Ind_uni.htm#army British Ruled India 1757\u20131947: Bibliography of Books Articles and Dissertations], accessed August 2010\n* [http://www.britishmilitaryhistory.co.uk British Military History \u2013 Including British Indian Army during WW2]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20061116203948/http://indianarmy.nic.in/arhist1.htm#British%20Era Indian Army: History: British Era] on the Indian Army website\n*[http://www.bbc.co.uk/radio4/history/standateast.shtml ''Stand at East'' \u2013 Mark Tully in a series of BBC audio programmes on the pre-independence Indian Army]\n*[htt